OL,3,CParents of terror attack victim recall
OL,4,Cmoment they were told of son's murder
OL,6,FThe couple also tried calling James'
OL,7,Ffriend, Joe Ritchie-Bennett, who he
OL,8,Fwas meeting up with in the park. He
OL,9,Falso did not answer his phone.
OL,11,FJan said: "I rang the police twice, I
OL,12,Frang the hospitals twice and nothing.
OL,13,FI thought no news is good news.
OL,15,F"We went upstairs to go to bed and
OL,16,FGary went to close the blind and he
OL,17,Fsaid Jan, there's a police car outside.
OL,19,F"Our lives just turned upside down
OL,20,Ffrom that night."
